 you\'re having difficulty with the dining options at college. Let\'s explore some strategies together. Have you considered bringing your own meals or trying out nearby restaurants that offer healthier alternatives?\n\n',NULL,'2025-03-25 10:27:50',0),(354,'user','I can\'t afford to eat outside everyday','eating disorder','2025-03-25 10:28:02',0),(355,'assistant','I understand that finances can be a concern. How about exploring budget-friendly options, like cooking simple meals at home or taking advantage of discounts offered by local eateries? It\'s important to find a balance between nutrition and affordability.\n\n',NULL,'2025-03-25 10:28:19',0),(356,'user','I live in a hostel where we cannot cook our own food','eating disorder','2025-03-25 10:28:31',0),(357,'assistant','That must be challenging for you, John Doe. Let\'s brainstorm some creative solutions. Have you considered bringing portable snacks or exploring nearby grocery stores to stock up on nutritious items? It might take some planning, but it could make a difference in your eating habits.\n\n',NULL,'2025-03-25 10:28:51',0),(358,'user','I live in a rather remote place. There aren\'t too many grocery stores nearby','normal','2025-03-25 10:29:10',1),(359,'assistant','I can imagine how frustrating that must be for you. In situations like these, it\'s important to prioritize self-care even with limited resources. Have you considered reaching out to the college cafeteria staff or speaking with your peers about potential solutions? Collaboration might lead to unexpected opportunities.\n\n',NULL,'2025-03-25 10:29:28',0),(360,'user','We have tried talking to the college staff multiple times. But they don\'t improve the quality of food. \n\nTo be honest, i just want a way to force myself to eat mess food. Can it be done?','eating disorder','2025-03-25 10:30:08',1),(361,'assistant','I understand your frustration, John Doe. It can be disheartening when efforts to improve the situation aren\'t yielding immediate resu